The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, December 24, 2003 				 ICI to sell division to CDC affiliate
 New Delhi, Dec. 23 (PTI):  The board of ICI India today recommended sale of its nitrocellulose  and trading business to an affiliate of CDC Plc of the UK  for a consideration of about Rs 75 crore.																								CDC (formerly Commonwealth Development Corporation) is an arm of the Department for International Development (DFID). CDC is on an acquisition spree in India. It recently acquired the Punjab governments stake in Punjab Tractors.																								The recommendation has to be approved by ICIs shareholders and out of Rs 75 crore, Rs 12.75 crore would be payable in three equal annual instalments, a statement said.																								The board believes that the proposal is in line with the strategy of focus on core business operations and is in the best interests of all shareholders, employees and customers, the company release said.																								The transaction would be completed in the next couple of months once necessary approvals were obtained. The deal includes transfer of 130 employees of the division.
